      "writtenOn": "2020-09-25T15:15:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a lot of boilerplate--and this is the minimal version; it\u0027s missing lots of stuff that would prevent it from being used in any actual STL algorithms (no reference/pointer typedefs, no operator\u003c, no subtraction, etc); I expect eventually we will want to flesh it out and fill in those limitations. \n\nWhat do you think about changing this so instead of\n    `for (Statement\u0026 s : block)`\nWe would do\n    `for (Statement\u0026 s : block.children())`\n\nI think this syntax is more clear anyway (we\u0027re iterating over one PART of the Block object; it\u0027s got more than just statements in it) and it lets us get this boilerplate out of Block and into a separate class, where we could even reuse it if we have a use case.\n\nNot required in this CL at all, and it\u0027s OK if you disagree, but please think it over?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "9d59366602dfdbae07332ae90657fe607797442b",
