      "message": "We don\u0027t actually have a valid BlockData in dest yet, we have a reference to a bag of uninitialized bytes. To have dest be a valid object, we need to do\n\n    new(\u0026dest) BlockData;\n\nAt that point your shared_ptr is constructed. Now you can just say\n    dest.fSymbolTable \u003d std::move(data.fSymbolTable);\n    dest.fIsScope \u003d data.fIsScope;\n\nOr this if you\u0027re willing to accept a little more action on the shared_ptr:\n    dest \u003d data;\n\nI don\u0027t know if this would work? But a man can dream:\n    dest \u003d std::move(data);",
